{"questionId":"22248","questionHtml":"<p>Which equation represents the standard enthalpy of formation of lithium oxide?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; 4Li (s) + O<sub>2 </sub>(g) → 2Li<sub>2</sub>O (s)</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; 2Li (s) +&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>O<sub>2 </sub>(g) → Li<sub>2</sub>O (s)</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; Li (s) + <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>O<sub>2 </sub>(g) →&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>Li<sub>2</sub>O (s)</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; Li (g) + <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>O<sub>2 </sub>(g) → <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>Li<sub>2</sub>O (g)</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"22248","referenceCode":"21N.1.sl.TZ0.15","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which equation represents the standard enthalpy of formation of lithium oxide? A. 4Li (s) + O2 (g) → 2Li2O (s) B. 2Li (s) + 12O2 (g) → Li2O (s) C. Li (s) + 14O2 (g) → 12Li2O (s) D.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"15","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.2 Hess’s Law","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}